HEADWORD: Oxidator
<hw>Ox"i*da`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
oxidizer.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A contrivance for causing a current of air to
impinge on the flame of the Argand lamp; -- called also
<altname>oxygenator</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1027 --></p>

<p><ent>Oxide</ent>⟦br⟧
